content: I've been updating the GForge trackers from our votes this week and I found 3 trackers from the Sept ballot that were in unexpected groups outside of the block votes, so they didn't end up getting voted on this week after all. :( They are GF#18554, GF#18606 and GF#18625, and they are now in the "Fit for teleconference" group. We also have GF#19307 to vote on again (as noted above). So we're going to need to plan to vote on the FHIR Tracker Issues call on Monday (which I will set up shortly). We will obviously need to have quorum on the call, and it should be according to our Main call quorum rules, so please join the call on Monday at 5:00 PM Eastern, if possible.
I guess Monday is the Columbus Day holiday in some parts of the US, so there may be some people who have the day off, but we will go ahead and have the call.
